======================================================================
Things to do before starting the project
Download node.js
npm came with node.js
https://nodejs.org/en/


=========================================================================

========================================================================
1)Terminal
Step 1) npm init (must do for every project)
-----------------------
generate package.json
-----------------------
Step 2) npm install express --save
        ( --save => save to dependencies)
        (-g => save to  global)
-----------------------
download express framework
-----------------------
Step 3) npm install nodemon --save-dev
------------------------
- constant running server ( if you change the code, it will automatically update without the need to re run the server)
If the installation above doesn't work for nodemon
----------------------------
try:   sudo npm install -g --force nodemon ( not recommended to use force)

Step 4) npm install socket.io --save(This project requires socket.io)
put this in the html: <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/socket.io/1.7.3/socket.io.js"></script>



=======================================================================


=======================================================================
Aftermath:
nodemon jsfile_name (To run node server)
=======================================================================
